Description: Interscape Technologies offers services to enterprises in designing and implementing enterprise storage system architecture.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Interscape Technologies offers services to enterprises in designing and implementing enterprise storage system architecture. It is a niche service provider in the area of performance analysis, performance troubleshooting, consolidation planning, migration planning, and capacity planning and trending for systems and storage area networks. The company offers a range of Performance Consulting Services (PCS), including performance analysis of enterprise storage systems; EMC Symmetrix, Clariion, and Centera; OS performance analysis for enterprise installation base; Solaris, Linux, AIX, and Windows; application tiering analysis; performance profiling for tiering recommendations; best fit RAID level analysis; bandwidth analysis DR replication for arrays and data centers; SAN consolidation planning; data migration planning; and detailed migration plans for source to target planning. It offers technical assessment services for storage performance analyzes storage arrays and provides metrics that will enable customers to understand performance of storage assets and its impact to applications by assessing, correcting, and streamlining IO throughput for better SLA and end-user experience; allocate storage resources based on integrated performance and capacity views for best optimization to leverage all storage resources in a balanced mode; trend for future capacity and performance projections across storage arrays; and accelerate troubleshooting of host level application issues with detailed visibility into back-end storage devices. Interscape Technologies’ Perfonics-enabled “Performance As A Service” are delivered as part of PAAS-PCS engagement on ad-hoc or recurring basis. Perfonics works with performance data from storage and systems for such as Work Load Analyzer, EMC Grabs, Hitachi Tuning Manager, Hitachi Configuration Data, IBM Tivoli Storage Manager, IBM SVC data, IO Stat, SAR, and Perfmon to provide an end-to-end performance view. Interscape Technologies was founded in 1997 by Alok Jain and is based in New Jersey, United States with presence in New Delhi, India.
